Mae Giraci https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mae_Giraci 0 Mae Georgia Giraci (22 January 1910 – 10 January 2006), also known as May Giraci, May Garcia, May Geraci, May Giracci, May Giracia and Tina Rossi, was an American child actress who appeared in silent films between 1915 and 1929. She was discovered by director Cecil B. DeMille and worked with him and his brother William C. DeMille. She died of colon cancer in 2006.
